cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the evolution of few-shot supervised and reinforcement learning mechanisms using deep learning algorithms. It also compares the Baldwin effect to a recent machine learning algorithm called MAML (Model Agnostic Meta-Learning), which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning algorithms in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO), which are related fields to the topic of meta learning.
